## UnusedDocParam

**Severity:** warning | **Type:** LiquidHtml

This check ensures that parameters defined in a partial's `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag are actually used within the partial body. A declared but unused parameter is almost always a mistake — either the parameter name was misspelled in the template, or the `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` declaration needs to be removed.

## Examples

### &#x2717; Incorrect Code Example (Avoid using this):

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} title - The card title
  @param {string} subtitle - The card subtitle
{% enddoc %}
<div class="card">
  <h2>{{ title }}</h2>
  {% comment %}subtitle is declared but never used{% endcomment %}
</div>
{% endraw %}
```

### &#x2713; Correct Code Example (Use this instead):

Either use the declared parameter:

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} title - The card title
  @param {string} subtitle - The card subtitle
{% enddoc %}
<div class="card">
  <h2>{{ title }}</h2>
  <p>{{ subtitle }}</p>
</div>
{% endraw %}
```

Or remove the unused declaration:

```liquid
{% raw %}
{% doc %}
  @param {string} title - The card title
{% enddoc %}
<div class="card">
  <h2>{{ title }}</h2>
</div>
{% endraw %}
```

## Configuration

The default configuration for this check:

```yaml
UnusedDocParam:
  enabled: true
  severity: warning
```

## Disabling This Check

This check is safe to disable if you use the `{% raw %}{% doc %}{% endraw %}` tag primarily for documentation purposes and intentionally declare parameters that serve as documentation only.

